                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/17497: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Hungary</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Pell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Budapest</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-13">December 13,
                            1941</date>.<lb/>[Received December 13—2:36 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>710. The Prime Minister informed me at 5:30 this afternoon that Hungary considers
                    war to exist between Hungary and United States. All codes destroyed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Pell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
